<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-latestspecs" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-actions" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1>Roadmap of Spec Implementation</h1>

  <p class="documentDescription">
    Based on the current specifications, their dependencies, priorities and
    statuses, Launchpad recommends the following implementation plan.
  </p>

  <p class="portalMessage" tal:condition="not: view/specPlan">
    Currently, there are no specifications for
    <span tal:replace="context/displayname">Ubuntu Hoary</span>
    that can be scheduled.
  </p>

  <tal:block condition="view/specPlan">
    <h2>Implementation Strategy</h2>

    <p>
      The following specifications should be implemented in the order given.
      This will ensure that most important specifications are implemented
      first, and that specification dependencies are respected.
    </p>

      <div tal:repeat="spec view/specPlan"
           tal:replace="structure spec/@@+listing-detailed" />
  </tal:block>

  <tal:block condition="view/danglingSpecs">
    <h2>Dangling Specifications</h2>

    <p>
      The following specifications are "dangling", in that they are currently
      in a state which cannot be scheduled. For example, they may have
      circular dependencies.
    </p>

      <div tal:repeat="spec view/danglingSpecs"
           tal:replace="structure spec/@@+listing-detailed" />
  </tal:block>

</div>
</body>
</html>
